<TITLE> DESCO to install pre-paid metres in capital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 28 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka Electric Supply Company will install 12,000 pre-paid metres for city dwellers within three months, the government announced on Thursday. The decision came in a meeting between state minister for energy and power Shamsul Haq Tuku and Desco officials, Electricity would be saved and system loss reduced, which would ultimately ease consumers' sufferings once pre-paid metres were launched, said the minister. The state-owned company supplies power to nearly 4 lakh consumers at Kafrul, Kalayapur, Pallabi, Baridhara, Uttara and Tongi areas. It aims to install a total of 40,000 pre-paid metres in these areas within six months. The chairman of the Power Develoment Board Alamgir Kabir, managing director of Desco Saleh Ahmed and joint-secretary of the power ministry Wahid Hossain attended the meeting. bdn
